    "product_framing": "### One-liner\n\nA compliance-first execution platform that evaluates every request before any side effects, executes actions only through a platform-owned worker identity, and produces an audit trail for every decision and outcome.\n\n### Target users / customers\n\n- Security and compliance leads who need guardrails and evidence\n- Platform engineers who own approvals and execution controls\n- Auditors who need traceability and exportable records\n\n### Problem statement\n\nTeams want to automate work, but approvals are inconsistent, policies are scattered, and evidence is incomplete. The platform must provide a single governed path from request to decision to execution and evidence.\n\n### Value proposition\n\nCentral policy lifecycle with approval, deterministic evaluation before execution, controlled execution identity, and immediate evidence for review and export.\n\n---",
    "scope": "### In scope\n\n- Central policy catalog with versioning and lifecycle (draft, review, active, retired)\n- Evaluate every request before execution; denied requests return reasons\n- Execute allowed requests via a platform-owned worker identity\n- Record evidence for request, decision, execution, and outcome\n- Tenant administration and tenant-scoped retention and deletion controls\n\n### Out of scope\n\n- A general-purpose workflow programming environment\n- Distributed event-bus orchestration as the default posture\n- Data lake analytics and BI dashboards\n\n### Assumptions\n\n- First release is single-region and keeps the runtime simple\n- Shared storage is acceptable as long as tenant separation is enforced everywhere\n\n### Dependencies\n\n- Organization identity provider for authentication (OIDC or SAML)\n- Notification channel (email or chat) in a later phase\n\n---",
    "quality_attributes": "| Attribute | Target / SLO | Measurement / Evidence | Notes |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| Availability | 99.9 percent | Uptime checks and incident log | Single region initially |\n| Latency | p95 300ms for evaluation calls | API metrics | Keep evaluation deterministic |\n| Security | Least privilege and audit trail | Security checklist and scan results | Admin actions audited |\n| Privacy | Tenant separation | Access logs and data inventory | Tenant-scoped exports |\n\n---",
    "constraints": "| Constraint | Type (Business/Tech/Legal) | Rationale | Notes |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| Evaluate every request before execution | Business | Guardrails are core value | Denials include reasons |\n| Execute only via platform-owned worker identity | Security | Prevent direct end-user side effects | Maintain attribution |\n| Tenant separation in data access layer | Tech | Avoid cross-tenant leaks | Tenant key required |\n| Evidence captured for request, decision, outcome | Compliance | Traceability | Evidence is immediate |\n\n---"
  },
  "posture": {
    "format": "table",
    "questions": [
      {
        "question_id": "PP-01",
        "question": "PP-01",
        "answer": "MVP"
      },
      {
        "question_id": "PP-02",
        "question": "PP-02",
        "answer": "Confidential"
